id: pm-r9ei
title: Fix Grafana RabbitMQ queue panel metric selector mismatch
description: "Telemetry overview dashboard queue panels query rabbitmq_queue_messages{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"} and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"}, but current Prometheus series on the remote stack have no queue label, so the panel query returns empty data despite non-zero queue depth."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: external-audit,grafana,observability,pm-cli,prometheus,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T09:57:02.619Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Grafana queue panels render live queue depth and unacked values in production by aligning panel queries with actual metric labels (or by exposing the queue label in exporter config).
parent: pm-lnq3
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-lnq3,parent,"2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z",codex-agent,null
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'Grafana rabbitmq queue dashboard metric label' --limit 10; pm search 'queue label rabbitmq_queue_messages' --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Net-new because no open item currently tracks dashboard query label mismatch between Prometheus RabbitMQ series and Grafana queue panel selectors."
  "2026-04-26T09:57:02.619Z",codex-agent,"Remote evidence 2026-04-26: Prometheus query rabbitmq_queue_messages returns value 3 and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked returns value 3, but both series are exported without queue label in metric metadata. Dashboard expressions filtering queue=pm.telemetry.events therefore return empty vectors and hide active queue backlog."
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
